rComments: She is a brilliant professor. Honestly, going to her class was an intense yet intellectually inspiring experience. I have had sleepless nights trying to keep up with the fast pace and heavy readings each week. However, it was such a rewarding effort. She is generous, gives wonderful feedback, rigorous, and known as a resident "genius." Don't miss!

One of the best profs I've ever had and can ever imagine having. Brilliant, engaging, compassionate, and funny, with a pedagogic talent for making complex theories incredibly lucid, she teaches courses which are a student's dream come true. Generous with grading, she will nonetheless push you to be a better writer, a better thinker, a better human being.
